<br>
  OK now , Granted shamans have buffs , do you think any high-end player shaman is gonna make the 20k or so that it'd cost him/her for a primal avatar buff ?? NO , or even better; the going price for Torpor on Drinal is 50K, anyone wanna pay me 1k for a shot of torpor ?? Didn't think so.  <br>
<br>
   Now, Shaman also have alchemy, it's not cheap; every INT caster has INSTANT claim to research items that drop in groups as a given rule. Most shamans will give a free SoW(that or a druid) plus the SoW boots  , so that money maker flies out the window.. Most high-end melee have there Velious ring quests in process so there's a no-go on DS potions too;  Extended Kei comes free almost anytime of anyday in the nexus (no need for them mana potions); and us shaman buff our groups for free so WTF are people gonna spend money on that for ???  <br>
<br>
   PLAIN AND SIMPLE; just like research most Alchemy potions will help the class  itself rather than make them money, on the rare occasion I find people in the need for the potions I hand them out anyhow or just give them the buff if I have it. <br>
<br>
    Next time you're on a raid or in a group and you die cause the Clerics were healing the tanks , ask yourself if you'd have live had you combined the materials for a torpor for free or cheap ;  better yet when your spells wont land , wonder about Malo ..... HMMMMMM<br>
<br>
<br>
  Anyhow if anyone made these points please forgive me, I just hate all this &quot;This class deserves this and that one doesn't BS&quot; if you think one class is getting a free ride then play that class and find out please ... TY<br>
<br>
<br>
 Marias Spiritrider<br>
